  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Long term disease management is essential for Ankylosing Spondylitis (AS), a chronic
      progressive systemic inflammatory disease of the axial skeleton. Extensive information about
      the disease is a necessary first step. An education program for AS was implemented to improve
      inpatient medical rehabilitation. In a controlled quasi-experimental multicentric study the
      efficacy of this program was analysed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
